Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Interfaces
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
  • Deprecated Interfaces 
    Interface and Description
    com.google.crypto.tink.Catalogue
    Catalogues are no longer supported.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetManager.add(KeyHandle, KeyAccess)
    Use KeysetManager.add(KeyHandle) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetManager.add(KeyTemplate)
    This method takes a KeyTemplate proto, which is an internal implementation detail. Please use the add method that takes a KeyTemplate POJO.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.addCatalogue(String, Catalogue<?>)
    Catalogues are no longer supported.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetManager.addNewKey(KeyTemplate, boolean)
    Please use KeysetManager.add(com.google.crypto.tink.proto.KeyTemplate). This method adds a new key and when asPrimary is true immediately promotes it to primary. However, when you do keyset rotation, you almost never want to make the new key primary, because old binaries don't know the new key yet.
    com.google.crypto.tink.PrimitiveSet.addPrimitive(P, Keyset.Key)
    use Builder.addPrimitive or Builder.addPrimaryPrimitive instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.tinkkey.KeyHandle.createFromKey(KeyData, KeyTemplate.OutputPrefixType)
    Use the KeyHandle(TinkKey, KeyAccess) constructor instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetHandle.createFromKey(KeyHandle, KeyAccess)
    Use KeysetManager.withEmptyKeyset().add(keyHandle) .setPrimary(keyHandle.getId()).getKeysetHandle() instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetHandle.generateNew(KeyTemplate)
    This method takes a KeyTemplate proto, which is an internal implementation detail. Please use the generateNew method that takes a KeyTemplate POJO.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getCatalogue(String)
    Catalogues are no longer supported.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getKeyManager(String)
    Use getKeyManager(typeUrl, Primitive.class) or getUntypedKeyManager typeUrl instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getPrimitive(KeyData)
    Use getPrimitive(keyData, Primitive.class) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getPrimitive(String, byte[])
    Use getPrimitive(typeUrl, serializedKey, Primitive.class) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getPrimitive(String, ByteString)
    Use getPrimitive(typeUrl, serializedKey, Primitive.class instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.getPrimitive(String, MessageLite)
    Use getPrimitive(typeUrl, key, P.class) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.PrimitiveSet.newPrimitiveSet(Class<P>)
    use PrimitiveSet.Builder instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetManager.promote(int)
    use setPrimary
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.registerKeyManager(String, KeyManager<P>)
    use registerKeyManager(KeyManager<P>)
    com.google.crypto.tink.Registry.registerKeyManager(String, KeyManager<P>, boolean)
    use registerKeyManager(KeyManager<P>, boolean)
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetHandle.Builder.removeAt(int)
    Use KeysetHandle.Builder.deleteAt(int) or KeysetHandle.Builder.getAt(int) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.KeysetManager.rotate(KeyTemplate)
    Please use KeysetManager.add(com.google.crypto.tink.proto.KeyTemplate). This method adds a new key and immediately promotes it to primary. However, when you do keyset rotation, you almost never want to make the new key primary, because old binaries don't know the new key yet.
    com.google.crypto.tink.PrimitiveSet.setPrimary(PrimitiveSet.Entry<P>)
    use Builder.addPrimaryPrimitive instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.proto.OutputPrefixType.valueOf(int)
    Use OutputPrefixType.forNumber(int) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.proto.KeyStatusType.valueOf(int)
    Use KeyStatusType.forNumber(int) instead.
    com.google.crypto.tink.proto.KeyData.KeyMaterialType.valueOf(int)
    Use KeyData.KeyMaterialType.forNumber(int) instead.
  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    com.google.crypto.tink.integration.gcpkms.GcpKmsClient()
    use GcpKmsClient.register(java.util.Optional<java.lang.String>, java.util.Optional<java.lang.String>)
    com.google.crypto.tink.integration.gcpkms.GcpKmsClient(String)
    use register
